<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════
     SECTION 1 — MUST-SEE LANDMARKS
════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div id="adventures">
<div class="ex-sec rv">
  <p class="ex-tag">✦ Must-See Attractions</p>
  <h2 class="ex-title">Dinosaur Country<br><em>Right Outside Your Door</em></h2>
  <p class="ex-intro">Vernal sits at the heart of one of the most geologically and paleontologically rich regions on earth. Here's what you absolutely can't miss.</p>

  <div class="cards-grid">

    <div class="card rv">
      <div class="card-img" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a3a5c, #2d5a3d);">
        <iframe class="card-video"
          src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/PoCN4Lo9Lkk?rel=0&amp;modestbranding=1&amp;playsinline=1"
          title="Dinosaur National Monument" frameborder="0"
          allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
          referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
        <span class="card-badge">⭐ Top Attraction</span>
        <span class="card-dist">~20 min</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <p class="card-cat">National Monument</p>
        <h3 class="card-name">Dinosaur National Monument</h3>
        <p class="card-desc">The crown jewel of Vernal. The Quarry Exhibit Hall puts you face-to-face with 1,500+ dinosaur bones still embedded in the cliff face — exactly where they were discovered. Add in canyon hikes, petroglyphs, and the Green River and you'll easily spend a full day here.</p>
        <a href="https://www.nps.gov/dino/index.htm" target="_blank" class="card-link">Plan Your Visit →</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card rv">
      <div class="card-img" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d3a1a, #3d5a2d);">
        <iframe class="card-video"
          src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/5fZUTR8bTec?rel=0&amp;modestbranding=1&amp;playsinline=1"
          title="Utah Field House of Natural History" frameborder="0"
          allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
          referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
        <span class="card-badge">Free Entry</span>
        <span class="card-dist">In Town</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <p class="card-cat">Museum · State Park</p>
        <h3 class="card-name">Utah Field House of Natural History</h3>
        <p class="card-desc">Walk through 200 million years of geologic time on the famous ramp exhibit. Life-sized dinosaur replicas greet you outside. Inside: real fossils, a working fossil prep lab you can watch through glass, and a knowledgeable staff that doubles as an informal visitor center.</p>
        <a href="https://stateparks.utah.gov/parks/field-house/" target="_blank" class="card-link">Learn More →</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card rv">
      <div class="card-img" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #3a1a2d, #5a2d3d);">
        <iframe class="card-video"
          src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/fwzaXWfuFdk?rel=0&amp;modestbranding=1&amp;playsinline=1"
          title="McConkie Ranch Petroglyphs" frameborder="0"
          allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
          referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
        <span class="card-badge">Hidden Gem</span>
        <span class="card-dist">~15 min</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <p class="card-cat">Historic Site · Petroglyphs</p>
        <h3 class="card-name">McConkie Ranch Petroglyphs</h3>
        <p class="card-desc">One of Utah's best-kept secrets. Near-life-sized Fremont culture figures carved into canyon sandstone — asks only a $5 donation. The main trail requires a short climb but rewards you with some of the most stunning ancient rock art in the American West.</p>
        <a href="https://utah.com/vernal/mcconkie-ranch-petroglyphs" target="_blank" class="card-link">Get Directions →</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card rv">
      <div class="card-img" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a2d3a, #0a4a6a);">
        <iframe class="card-video"
          src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/tktE4GbS9gQ?rel=0&amp;modestbranding=1&amp;playsinline=1"
          title="Flaming Gorge" frameborder="0"
          allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
          referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
        <span class="card-badge">Scenic Drive</span>
        <span class="card-dist">~40 min</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <p class="card-cat">National Recreation Area</p>
        <h3 class="card-name">Flaming Gorge</h3>
        <p class="card-desc">200,000+ acres of stunning red canyon, emerald reservoir, and world-class fishing. Boat, waterski, camp, hike, or simply drive the Flaming Gorge–Uintas National Scenic Byway. The dam tour is surprisingly fascinating. Often called "the crown of the Uinta Mountains."</p>
        <a href="https://www.fs.usda.gov/detail/ashley/recreation/?cid=fsm9_004244" target="_blank" class="card-link">Explore Flaming Gorge →</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card rv">
      <div class="card-img" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d1a3a, #1a3050);">
        <iframe class="card-video"
          src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/9F16EIFko60?rel=0&amp;modestbranding=1&amp;playsinline=1"
          title="Red Fleet State Park" frameborder="0"
          allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
          referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
        <span class="card-badge">Easy Hike</span>
        <span class="card-dist">~10 min</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <p class="card-cat">State Park · Hiking</p>
        <h3 class="card-name">Red Fleet State Park</h3>
        <p class="card-desc">Known as "Little Lake Powell," Red Fleet offers a stunning sandstone lake setting. Hike the Dinosaur Trackway — a 3-mile round trip across sandstone formations to real 200-million-year-old dinosaur footprints, ending at a beautiful swimming spot on the reservoir. Kayak rentals available.</p>
        <a href="https://stateparks.utah.gov/parks/red-fleet/" target="_blank" class="card-link">Park Info →</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card rv">
      <div class="card-img" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #3a2d1a, #6a4a0a);">
        <iframe class="card-video"
          src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/m64J-ovzTf4?rel=0&amp;modestbranding=1&amp;playsinline=1"
          title="Fantasy Canyon" frameborder="0"
          allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
          referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
        <span class="card-badge">Wow Factor</span>
        <span class="card-dist">~1 hr</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <p class="card-cat">Scenic Wonder</p>
        <h3 class="card-name">Fantasy Canyon</h3>
        <p class="card-desc">One of the most bizarre and beautiful places in Utah — otherworldly sandstone formations that look like they belong on another planet. About an hour south of Vernal, accessible by passenger car. Visit near sunset for extraordinary photography. Small but absolutely unforgettable.</p>
        <a href="https://www.blm.gov/visit/fantasy-canyon" target="_blank" class="card-link">Directions →</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card rv">
      <div class="card-img" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a3a1a, #2a4a3a);">
        <iframe class="card-video"
          src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/hmKWG8GZBiw?rel=0&amp;modestbranding=1&amp;playsinline=1"
          title="Moonshine Arch" frameborder="0"
          allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
          referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
        <span class="card-badge">Easy Trail</span>
        <span class="card-dist">~8 min</span>
      </div>
      <div class="card-body">
        <p class="card-cat">Hiking · Nature</p>
        <h3 class="card-name">Moonshine Arch</h3>
        <p class="card-desc">A stunning 40-foot-tall, 85-foot-wide sandstone arch just 8 miles from town — easy 2-mile round-trip hike with views of Steinaker Reservoir. Shaded caverns behind the arch are perfect for a picnic. Moab doesn't have a monopoly on Utah arches — this one is spectacular and never crowded.</p>
        <a href="https://www.alltrails.com/trail/us/utah/moonshine-arch-trail" target="_blank" class="card-link">Trail Info →</a>
